Title: The Killer
Description: While Mike is at an airport in a small town, a man tries to kill him. However, when he reports the incident to the local police, they dismiss it as a publicity stunt.
Short Description: While Mike is at an airport in a small town, a man tries to kill him.

Title: Eyewitness
Description: Mike uses a picture to prove an old man's innocence.
Short Description: Mike uses a picture to prove an old man's innocence.

Title: The Man Below
Description: Mike suspects a man recently pushed into a well is a man he was hired to prove is still alive. Before he can prove the two men are the same, Mike must convince miners he is still alive, since no one will risk their lives to bring up a corpse.

Title: Play Belles' Toll
Description: Mike learns an acquaintance of his was working for a high class escort service.
Short Description: Mike learns an acquaintance of his was working for a high class escort service.

Title: My Fair Deadly
Description: Mike seeks a killer at the World's Fair in Brussels.
Short Description: Mike seeks a killer at the World's Fair in Brussels.

Title: Music to Die By
Description: A disc jockey runs into trouble with a syndicate that controls a stable of singers.
Short Description: A disc jockey runs into trouble with a syndicate that controls a stable of singers.

Title: For Sale: Death Bed-Used
Description: Mike is shocked when he discovers the identity of a psychotic, knife-wielding killer.
Short Description: Mike is shocked when he discovers the identity of a psychotic, knife-wielding killer.

Title: The Case of the Cunningham Heritage
Description: After his return from Afghanistan, Dr. Watson meets Sherlock Holmes and is recruited as his assistant. Together they investigate a murder, with a young lady as the prime suspect. Holmes finds the real murderer and learns his motive.
Short Description: After his return from Afghanistan, Dr. Watson meets Sherlock Holmes and is recruited as his assistant. Together they investigate a murder, with a young lady as the prime suspect.

Title: The Case of Lady Beryl
Description: Inspector Lestrade and Dr. Watson investigate a murder at the Beryl residence, but to their surprise get a confession from Lady Beryl, which Holmes does not credit. Holmes recreates the crime scene to expose the actual murderer.
Short Description: Inspector Lestrade and Dr. Watson investigate a murder at the Beryl residence.

Title: The Case of the Shoeless Engineer
Description: Escape artist Harry Crocker begs Holmes to help clear his name of a murder he didn't do, although clues seem to point to him. The murderer is revealed to have been jealous of the victim's relationship with Harry.
Short Description: Escape artist Harry Crocker begs Holmes to help clear his name of a murder he didn't do, although clues seem to point to him.

Title: The Case of Harry Crocker
Description: The story follows that of "The Adventure of the Engineer's Thumb," but Hatherley loses a shoe rather than his thumb and escapes with the aid of the woman, Ruth Connors. Two co-conspirators are captured by Lestrade, with the assistance of Holmes.
Short Description: The story follows that of "The Adventure of the Engineer's Thumb," but Hatherley loses a shoe rather than his thumb.
